Make the canvases for each plot¶

In [2]:
File_Fits = ROOT.TFile.Open("../output/FitterOutput.root", "READ")

Canv_Fits = {}
Canv_Fits["Ds"] = ROOT.TCanvas("c_Ds", "", 900, 1200)
Canv_Fits["K"]  = ROOT.TCanvas("c_K", "", 900, 1200)
Canv_Fits["Ds"].Divide(3,4)
Canv_Fits["K"] .Divide(3,4)

Legends = {}
Texts = []

for Mode in ["K", "Ds"]:
    it = 1
    for resolution in np.linspace(0.3, 1.3, 11):
        canvas = File_Fits.Get("c_Fit_{mode}_{resolution}".format(mode = Mode, resolution = resolution))
        Canv_Fits[Mode].cd(it)
        for prim in canvas.GetListOfPrimitives():
            if prim.GetName() == "TPave":
                Legends[Mode] = prim.Clone()
                canvas.GetListOfPrimitives().Remove(prim)
                break
        Text = ROOT.TPaveText(0.02, 0.8, 0.3, 0.98, "NDC")
        Text.AddText("{0} #sigma LHCb".format(resolution))
        Text.SetBorderSize(0)
        Text.SetFillColor(0)
        canvas.DrawClonePad()
        
        Text.Draw()
        Texts += [Text]
        it+=1
        
    Canv_Fits[Mode].cd(12)
    Legends[Mode].SetX1(0)
    Legends[Mode].SetX2(1)
    Legends[Mode].SetY1(0)
    Legends[Mode].SetY2(1)
    Legends[Mode].Draw()

canv_Budget = ROOT.TCanvas("c_graph", "", 900, 900)
Graph_K.SetMaximum(15)
Graph_K.SetMinimum(0)
Graph_K.Draw()
Graph_K.Fit("pol1")

canv_Budget.Draw()

box_1 = ROOT.TBox(1.118, 0, 1.195, 15)
box_2 = ROOT.TBox(0.736, 0, 0.904, 15)
Line1 = ROOT.TLine(1, 0, 1, 15)

Line1.SetLineColor(3)

box_1.SetFillColorAlpha(3, 0.2)
box_2.SetFillColorAlpha(3, 0.2)

box_1.Draw()
box_2.Draw()
Line1.Draw()
canv_Budget.Print("Error_Budget_K.pdf")
